(43, 6, 49, 4, 26, 65, 65, 'did eat manna in the wilderness', 'Manna and Wilderness Death', 'This connection highlights the fate of those who ate manna in the wilderness, as both passages emphasize that they died in that same wilderness. John 6:49 references the fathers who ate manna, while Numbers 26:65 states that they shall surely die in the wilderness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
