(43, 6, 49, 43, 6, 31, 31, 'manna in the wilderness', 'Manna in the Wilderness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of manna provided in the wilderness. They reflect on the historical experience of the Israelites receiving bread from heaven, highlighting the contrast between their physical sustenance and mortality.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 49, 43, 6, 58, 58, 'your fathers did eat manna', 'Manna and Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between the manna eaten by the fathers, which led to death, and the bread from heaven that grants eternal life. This connection highlights the significance of the new bread Jesus offers compared to the old.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
